        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(models): dedupe implicit CLI runtime aliases",
        "body": "Summary\n- Prune implicit CLI runtime alias provider rows from `/models` provider data when the canonical provider already owns the same model.\n- Preserve explicit legacy CLI runtime refs, including configured exact refs and wildcard/provider-visible cases, so existing user configs do not disappear.\n- Preserve explicit full-catalog CLI runtime provider browsing: `/models claude-cli all` still lists `claude-cli/*` rows even when canonical `anthropic/*` rows exist.\n- Add regression coverage for duplicate alias pruning, explicit legacy preservation, canonical models routed through CLI runtime policy, and the explicit CLI provider `all` browse path.\n\nVerification\n- Rebuilt the PR branch cleanly on top of upstream `main` and force-pushed only the fork branch with `--force-with-lease`; the PR diff is back to the intended three files: `src/agents/model-runtime-aliases.ts`, `src/auto-reply/reply/commands-models.ts`, and `src/auto-reply/reply/commands-models.test.ts`.\n- `pnpm install --frozen-lockfile`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.auto-reply-reply.config.ts src/auto-reply/reply/commands-models.test.ts` passed on the clean branch: 1 file, 33 tests.\n- `pnpm exec oxlint src/auto-reply/reply/commands-models.ts src/auto-reply/reply/commands-models.test.ts src/agents/model-runtime-aliases.ts` passed on the clean branch.\n- `git diff --check` passed before the clean commit.\n- `git diff --check HEAD^..HEAD` passed after the clean commit.\n\nLive behavior proof\n- Exact build/SHA tested: `0f814c1792bd048e39af89415a6b158835d1b766`.\n- Real environment used: local terminal source checkout on macOS Darwin 25.3.0 arm64, Node `v25.6.1`, pnpm `11.2.2`.\n- Live path exercised: terminal invocation of the actual `/models` command handler with synthetic terminal sender metadata and isolated workspace `/tmp/openclaw-proof-85982`. No unit-test mocks were used for the proof commands.\n- Command flow 1 exercised: `/models`.\n- Observed result after patch: default provider browse no longer lists implicit CLI alias providers beside canonical providers:\n\n```text\nCOMMAND /models\nProviders:\n- anthropic (4)\n- arcee (3)\n- google (6)\n- openai (16)\n- openrouter (3)\n- xai (9)\n\nUse: /models <provider>\nSwitch: /model <provider/model>\nEND COMMAND /models\n```\n\n- Command flow 2 exercised: `/models claude-cli all`.\n- Observed result after patch: explicit CLI runtime provider full-catalog browse still works and lists `claude-cli/*` rows:\n\n```text\nCOMMAND /models claude-cli all\nModels (claude-cli · 🔑 token (anthropic:manual)) — showing 1-4 of 4 (page 1/1)\n- claude-cli/claude-opus-4-6\n- claude-cli/claude-opus-4-7\n- claude-cli/claude-opus-4-8\n- claude-cli/claude-sonnet-4-6\n\nSwitch: /model <provider/model>\nEND COMMAND /models claude-cli all\n```\n\nBefore/after symptom evidence\n- Before this update, ClawSweeper identified that pruning ran even for `view: \"all\"`, so explicit CLI provider browse could lose its CLI rows.\n- After this update, pruning is skipped for `options.view === \"all\"`; the terminal proof above shows `/models` dedupes implicit providers while `/models claude-cli all` still works.\n\nRemaining proof gaps\n- I did not run the full repository test suite.\n- I did not capture a live Telegram Desktop recording; the proof is terminal output from the affected `/models` command path.\n\nFixes #83342\n",
